BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Extra Event / Mimořádná akce
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Prague:20260512T180000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Prague:20260512T185500
DTSTAMP:20260421T040651Z
UID:4104579574d921c6@cal-scraper
DESCRIPTION:Science is all around us – what have women invented? Pavla H
 ubálková\, Ondřej Heigl\, Tomáš Přibyl\, Julie Vašků\, Jana Kláno
 vá\, Lucie Vidovićová\, Radek Matuška\, and others. Come enjoy an inte
 ractive evening at the planetarium in Brno. Many scientific discoveries ar
 e made by women – yet their contributions often remain invisible. In the
  first part\, we will go to the stars and present female scientists who fo
 llow the motto "sky is NOT the limit" and whose discoveries change the wor
 ld. In the second part\, a game awaits you for the book Invisible Women in
  Science\, interactive booths\, decoding activities in the planetarium\, a
 nd finally\, colors and sparks at a chemical show. The event is for all Ea
 rthlings who love to explore. Everyone will find something\, whether they 
 feel at home in a planetarium or if it will be their first time.\nTickets:
  https://www.brnoid.cz/cs/hvezdarna-vstupenky?e=32236\n\n⚠️ Unofficial
  source – verify details on the organizer's website. Auto-translated via
  Azure OpenAI.\n\n---\n\nPrice/Cena: cena: 50\nNote: End time is approxima
 te (duration estimated at 55min)\nDatum: 12/5/2026\, 18:00\n\n---\n\nVěda
  je všude kolem nás – co vše vymyslely ženy?Pavla Hubálková\, Ond
 řej Heigl\, Tomáš Přibyl\, Julie Vašků\, Jana Klánová\, Lucie Vido
 vićová\, Radek Matuška a další.Přijďte si užít interaktivní podv
 ečer v brněnském planetáriu.Za mnoha vědeckými objevy stojí ženy 
 – jen jejich přínos často zůstává neviditelný. V první části v
 yrazíme ke hvězdám a představíme vědkyně\, které se řídí mottem
  „sky is NOT the limit“ a svými objevy mění svět.V druhé části 
 na vás čeká hra o knížku Neviditelné ženy ve vědě\, interaktivní
  stánky\, šifrovačka planetáriem a nakonec barvy a třesky při chemic
 ké show.Akce je pro všechny pozemšťany\, které baví objevovat. Na sv
 é si přijdou ti\, kteří jsou v planetáriu jako doma i ti\, pro které
  to bude poprvé.\nVstupenky: https://www.brnoid.cz/cs/hvezdarna-vstupenky
 ?e=32236\n\n⚠️ Neoficiální zdroj – ověřte si detaily na webu po
 řadatele.
LOCATION:digitárium - veřejnost
URL:
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Lecture / Přednáška
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Prague:20260519T193000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Prague:20260519T211000
DTSTAMP:20260421T040651Z
UID:21db3a02d582b613@cal-scraper
DESCRIPTION:Andrea M. Ghez\, From the Possibility to the Certainty of a Su
 permassive Black Hole. Learn about new developments in the study of superm
 assive black holes. Through the capture and analysis of twenty years of hi
 gh-resolution imaging\, the UCLA Galactic Center Group has moved the case 
 for a supermassive black hole at the center of our galaxy from a possibili
 ty to a certainty and provided the best evidence to date for the existence
  of these truly exotic objects. This was made possible with the first meas
 urements of stellar orbits around a galactic nucleus. Further advances in 
 state-of-the-art high-resolution imaging technology on the world’s large
 st telescopes have greatly expanded the power of using stellar orbits to s
 tudy black holes. Recent observations have revealed an environment around 
 the black hole that is quite unexpected (young stars where there should be
  none\, a lack of old stars where there should be many\, and a puzzling ne
 w class of objects). Continued measurements of the motions of stars have s
 olved many of the puzzles posed by these perplexing populations of stars. 
 This work provides insight into how black holes grow and the role that the
 y play in regulating the growth of their host galaxies. Measurements this 
 past year of stellar orbits at the Galactic Center have provided new insig
 ht into how gravity works near a supermassive hole\, a new and unexplored 
 regime for this fundamental force of nature.\nSuitable for serious enthusi
 asts of natural sciences\nTickets: https://www.brnoid.cz/cs/hvezdarna-vstu
 penky?e=32234\n\n⚠️ Unofficial source – verify details on the organi
 zer's website. Auto-translated via Azure OpenAI.\n\n---\n\nPrice/Cena: cen
 a: 70\nDatum: 19/5/2026\, 19:30\n\n---\n\nAndrea M. Ghez\, From the Possib
 ility to the Certainty of a Supermassive Black HoleLearn about new develop
 ments in the study of supermassive black holes. Through the capture and an
 alysis of twenty years of high-resolution imaging\, the UCLA Galactic Cent
 er Group has moved the case for a supermassive black hole at the center of
  our galaxy from a possibility to a certainty and provided the best eviden
 ce to date for the existence of these truly exotic objects. This was made 
 possible with the first measurements of stellar orbits around a galactic n
 ucleus. Further advances in state-of-the-art high-resolution imaging techn
 ology on the world’s largest telescopes have greatly expanded the power 
 of using stellar orbits to study black holes. Recent observations have rev
 ealed an environment around the black hole that is quite unexpected (young
  stars where there should be none\, a lack of old stars where there should
  be many\, and a puzzling new class of objects). Continued measurements of
  the motions of stars have solved many of the puzzles posed by these perpl
 exing populations of stars. This work provides insight into how black hole
 s grow and the role that they play in regulating the growth of their host 
 galaxies. Measurements this past year of stellar orbits at the Galactic Ce
 nter have provided new insight into how gravity works near a supermassive 
 hole\, a new and unexplored regime for this fundamental force of nature.\n
 vhodné pro vážné zájemce o přírodní vědy\nVstupenky: https://www.
 brnoid.cz/cs/hvezdarna-vstupenky?e=32234\n\n⚠️ Neoficiální zdroj –
  ověřte si detaily na webu pořadatele.
LOCATION:digitárium - veřejnost
URL:https://www.hvezdarna.cz/porad/odborne-prednasky/
END:VEVENT
